This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories as it deals with anomaly detection algorithms and their evaluation. It also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it discusses the strengths and weaknesses of various algorithms. Additionally, it involves data structures (cs.DS) as it creates a large corpus of anomaly detection benchmarks and discusses the relevance of features. Lastly, it involves software engineering (cs.SE) as it provides guidelines for future experimental design and discusses potential pitfalls in measuring success in this field.
